 (54,'MENU_ITEM',1200,100,'NO','Website Contributions','','<br />\r\n\r\n<h2> Contributions of Website Content</h2>\r\n\r\n<br />\r\n\r\n\r\n<p>\r\nContributions are always welcome, be they related to church or local community issues.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\nSubmissions should be sent to \r\n\r\n   <a href=\\\"javascript:mailPopUp(\\\'Webmaster@ChristChurchLye.org.uk\\\')\\\">\r\n    Webmaster@ChristChurchLye.org.uk\r\n   </a>\r\n\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\nAny contributions should be sent as attachments to emails as the website email popup window doesn\\\'t support attachments.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n<p>\r\nA few rules apply.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n\r\n <li>\r\n   Any item must be accompanied by an email address, and preferably a telephone number.\r\n </li>\r\n\r\n <li>\r\n   Pictures and graphical images will only be considered if in jpg or gif format. Images must be accompanied by a statement that the person submitting the image either owns the copyright to the image or provides a contact point for the copyright holder.\r\n </li>\r\n\r\n <li>\r\n   Similar rules apply to text submissions. Ideally text should be submitted in plain ASCII text. In reality we can cope with most proprietary word processing formats.\r\n </li>\r\n\r\n\r\n <li>\r\n   For both graphical images and text contributions anything vaguely contentious will be placed before the priest in charge  - Simon Falshaw - whose decision as to whether to include any submission is final. \r\n </li>\r\n\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n\r\n<br />\r\n\r\n<p>\r\nHowever, having got the legalese out of the way, We want this website to work, be current and be a useful resource for the Church and the Community.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\nThe more contributions the website receives, the better it gets and the more useful it is.\r\n</p>\r\n','RIGHT','2008-12-04'),
