 (63,'MENU_ITEM',200,200,'NO','Church Water Bill Petition','','<br />\r\n\r\n<h2>Water Charges</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\nWe have been advised that the water companies are starting to charge churches as businesses which is leading in some cases to enormous increases in charges.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n<p>\r\nSee this \r\n<a \r\nhref=\\\"http://www.telegraph.co.uk/opinion/main.jhtml?xml=/opinion/2008/10/11/do1105.xml\\\">\r\nDaily Telegraph\r\n</a>\r\narticle.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n<p>\r\nIf sufficient people sign the petition which can be found on the link below the water companies might be asked to change their minds.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\nIt would require at least 15,000 signatories to get noticed. As of Tuesday 2nd of September 2008 there where just above 11,000 signatories.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n<p>\r\nPlease go to \r\n<a href=\\\"http://petitions.pm.gov.uk/churchwaterbills\\\">http://petitions.pm.gov.uk/churchwaterbills</a>\r\nto declare your objection.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\n<b>\r\n<i>\r\nAs of Monday 24/11/2008 the number of signatories on the petition was 37,618\r\n</i>\r\n</b>\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\n<h4>The Closing Date for the Petition is Saturday December 6th.</h4>\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n','LEFT','2008-12-03'),
