 (77,'MENU_ITEM',600,200,'NO','Stourbridge Food Bank','http://www.blackcountryfoodbank.org.uk/','<br />\r\n\r\n<h2>\r\nStourbridge Food Bank\r\n</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\n<a href=\"http://www.chawnhillchurch.org.uk/Groups/67840/Chawn_Hill_Church/about_us/Community_Outreach/Food_Bank/Food_Bank.aspx\">\r\nFoodbank\r\n</a>\r\nLatest:\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\n<b>\r\nFriday 23rd April 2010\r\n</b>\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\nCurrently The Storehouse is running very low on food......\r\n<br /> \r\nIf no more donations were to come in from today, we could\r\nonly carry on feeding people for approx. 2 weeks.\r\n<br />\r\nWithout your donations of food and/or money this ministry\r\nwill not be able to continue.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\nOur shopping lists are posted on:\r\n<a href=\"http://www.blackcountryfoodbank.org.uk\">\r\nwww.blackcountryfoodbank.org.uk\r\n</a>\r\n- how can you help page\r\n</p> \r\n\r\n<p>\r\nWe\'re deperate for:\r\n<br />\r\nTinned Tomatoes, Peas, Carrots, Sweet Corn\r\n<br />\r\nInstant Mash\r\n<br />\r\nTinned Meat (hot dogs, meatballs)\r\n<br />\r\nUHT Milk\r\n<br />\r\nTinned Vegetarian Ready Meals (Macaroni Cheese, Vegetable Curry, Ravioli)\r\n<br />\r\nUHT Fruit Juice\r\n\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\n<b>\r\nThursday 21st January 2010\r\n</b>\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\nStock levels in the storehouse are adequate but we are\r\nextremely low on the following items:\r\n<br />\r\nCereal multi packs (we can divide these down)\r\n<br />\r\nWeetabix (small)\r\n<br />\r\nTinned Potatoes (large and small)\r\n<br />\r\nCoffee (small jars).\r\n<br />\r\nInstant Noodles (small).\r\n<br />\r\nFruit Juice (regular & small).\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\nNon Food:\r\n<br />\r\nAnti Bacterial Gel\r\n<br />\r\nShaving Gel\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n<p>\r\n<b>\r\nSaturday 1st August 2009\r\n</b>\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\nSince we started supporting the Foodbank\r\nregularly Christ Church has donated a \r\nwhopping 572.4kg of food and goods. \r\nThat would have fed approximately the equivalent of 572\r\nmeals! Don\'t stop now. \r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\nHow long will it take to\r\ndouble this figure? The need continues to be great. Stourbridge\r\nhas had one of the greatest increases in the number of people\r\nunemployed during the past year.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n<p>\r\n<b>\r\nFriday 13th of February\r\n</b>\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\nChrist Church sent 124Kg of supplies to the \r\nStourbridge Food Bank.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\n<a href=\"http://www.chawnhillchurch.org.uk/Groups/67840/Chawn_Hill_Church/about_us/Community_Outreach/Food_Bank/Food_Bank.aspx\">\r\nStourbridge Food Bank \r\n</a>\r\n\r\nwould like to say thank you for the items that have been donated since Wendy was here. They have a list of what they are actually short of.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\nThese include: Noodles (cheap ones), Potatoes tinned and dried. Rice Pudding (tinned), Mild UHT, Fruit (tinned), Fruit Juice UHT, Pasta/Cooking Sauces, tinned/jars or sachets, Breakfast Cereals, Biscuits, Tinned Tomatoes, healthy snacks, raisins/cereal bars etc. Toothbrushes, tissues, Deodorant, Shampoo (small sizes), Nappies all sizes.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\nEven though the items mentioned are in short supply please don\'t forget all the other items that were on the shopping list, if everyone bought tomatoes then other items would be come short. Shop sensibly. \r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\nAnyone able to donate tinned and dried goods can call \r\n<br />\r\n01384 441519 or 01384 397287\r\n</p>\r\n','LEFT','2012-04-09'),
