 (90,'MENU_ITEM',400,1700,'NO','Christ Church Recipe Book','','<br />\r\n\r\n<h2>Christ Church Recipe Book</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\nAt the end of a very enjoyable Eritrean evening where we tasted Feven\'s wonderful cooking, I jokingly suggested to Simon that with such a diverse congregation, we should have our own recipe book.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\nSince then I have been thinking more about the idea and it has grown on me. Not only do we have a good variety of theological, cultural and ethnic backgrounds represented in our Church, we have some very good cooks. At various bring and share meals, celebrations for baptisms and confirmations, national evenings, alpha courses and so on, I have tasted some lovely food. \r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\nI would therefore like to produce a recipe book that:- lets people recreate some of the meals we have eaten, celebrates the fact that we are one body in Christ but made up from a whole variety of parts and focuses on particular areas of the world and their food, politics and prayer needs. Whether we produce it to sell and raise money for the church I don\'t know yet, but I\'d like to do it anyway and so, if people are interested, then please talk to me at church or e-mail me.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\nI am happy to produce it but will need lots of contributions to make it work. \r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\nChris Milne. \r\n\r\n<form action=\"index.php?displaypage=mailform.php\" method=\"post\">\r\n<input type=\"hidden\" name=\"emailrecipient\" \r\nvalue=\"chris.milne@christchurchlye.org.uk\">\r\n<input type=\"submit\" value=\"Email\">\r\n</form>\r\n\r\n</p>','LEFT','2009-06-20'),
 (94,'MENU_ITEM',450,1200,'NO','Past Events - Pictures and Notes','','<br />\r\n\r\n<h2>\r\nPast Events\r\n</h2>\r\n\r\n\r\n<p>\r\nA look at past events.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n\r\n\r\n<li>\r\n<p>\r\nAugust 2009\r\n<br />\r\n<a href=\\\"http://www.christchurchlye.org.uk/index.php?displaypage=internal.html&rowid=108\\\" >\r\nSummer Barbeque\r\n</a>\r\n</p>\r\n</li>\r\n\r\n<li>\r\n<p>\r\nOpen door Strawberry Lunch\r\n<br />\r\n<a href=\\\"http://www.christchurchlye.org.uk/index.php?displaypage=internal.html&rowid=105\\\" >\r\nOpen Door\r\n</a>\r\n</p>\r\n</li>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<li>\r\n<p>\r\nKiver Edge\r\n<br />\r\n<a href=\\\"http://www.christchurchlye.org.uk/index.php?displaypage=internal.html&rowid=96\\\" >\r\nA walk in the park\r\n</a>\r\n</p>\r\n</li>\r\n\r\n\r\n<li>\r\n<p>\r\nSunday March 15th 2009 \r\n<br />\r\n<a href=\\\"http://www.christchurchlye.org.uk/index.php?displaypage=internal.html&rowid=92\\\" >\r\nBring and Share Lunch\r\n</a>\r\n</p>\r\n</li>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n</ul>','RIGHT','2011-03-20'),
 (95,'MENU_ITEM',400,500,'NO','The Big Lunch','','<br />\r\n\r\n<h2>\r\nGrowing churches sit down for the Big Lunch\r\n</h2>\r\n                       \r\n<p>\r\nChurches are being encouraged to grow their own produce - or use local food - and break bread with their own community as part of the Eden Project\'s nationwide \'Big Lunch\' on 19 July.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\nLaunched this month, to give growers and organisers time to prepare for the big day on July 19, the Big Lunch aims to bring communities - both rural and urban - together to create a new sense of neighbourhood and make the most of what they have on their own doorstep. \r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\n\r\nDudley Council \r\n<a href=\"http://www.dudley.gov.uk/index.asp?pgid=2351\">\r\nAllotments\r\n</a>\r\nInformation \r\n\r\n<br />\r\n\r\n<div style=\"float:right; margin-left:1em; margin-top:1em;\">\r\n\r\n\r\n<div id=\"slideshow\" style=\"padding-left:1em; padding-bottom:1em;\">\r\n\r\n    <div class=\"active\">\r\n        <img src=\"jpgs/slide/allotments/allotment001.jpg\" alt=\"Slideshow Image 1\" />\r\n    </div>\r\n    \r\n    <div>\r\n        <img src=\"jpgs/slide/allotments/allotment002.jpg\" alt=\"Slideshow Image 2\" />\r\n    </div>\r\n    \r\n    <div>\r\n        <img src=\"jpgs/slide/allotments/allotment003.jpg\" alt=\"Slideshow Image 3\" />\r\n    </div>\r\n    \r\n    <div>\r\n        <img src=\"jpgs/slide/allotments/allotment004.jpg\" alt=\"Slideshow Image 4\" />\r\n    </div>\r\n\r\n    <div>\r\n        <img src=\"jpgs/slide/allotments/allotment005.jpg\" alt=\"Slideshow Image 4\" />\r\n    </div>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\n\r\nWith a Christian presence in every community the Church of England is keen to tap into the event and support community ventures or host their own. \r\nChurch members at St Mary The Boltons in Chelsea have already planted herbs and vegetables for their homegrown \'loaves and fishes\' meal they plan to host as part of the Earls Court Festival. The Revd Ruth Lampard, associate vicar of St Mary The Boltons, said: \"We are delighted to support \'the simple act of community\' objective of the Big Lunch project. Through The Boltons Big Lunch we want to reach out to the local community, especially the lonely and isolated, and share good food and sunshine. We are aiming for a festival picnic atmosphere.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\nDr Jill Hopkinson, the National Rural Officer for the Church of England, said this would be a chance for churches to celebrate with their communities. .\"The rural church has always been deeply involved in its local community and this is a great way to show it. The Big Lunch is an opportunity for rural churches of all denominations to work together to encourage gardeners, support local farmers and food producers and have fun with the whole rural community.\"\r\nDavid Shreeve, the Church of England\'s Environment Adviser, said: \"Many churches already organise parish lunches for their congregations on Sundays. The Big Lunch brings the opportunity to extend these and offer a welcome to others in their communities. If this can include using church land to produce some of the food then that would be a real bonus.\"\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\nTips from the Royal Horticultural Society are provided for Big Lunch enthusiasts who want to grow their own produce or plant ahead for the 2010 event - carrots can still be planted this April in time for the July 2009 event.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\n<b>\r\nAND IN LYE......\r\n</b>\r\n The Lye and Wollescote Partnership is planning a Big Lunch event.  You may also want to organise something with neighbours on your street.... Its a great opportunity \r\n</p>','LEFT','2009-07-19'),
